======================================================================
PART 2: INDEPENDENCE COMPLEX OF Ω(T)
======================================================================

For each tournament T, Ω(T) is the conflict graph of odd cycles.
Ind(Ω(T)) is the simplicial complex of independent sets.
χ(Ind) = I(Ω, -1) — the Euler characteristic.
H(T) = I(Ω, 2) — the tournament evaluation.
The DEFORMATION x: -1 → 2 bridges topology and counting.

--- n = 3 ---

  Topology of Ind(Ω(T)) grouped by H:
  H=1 (6 tournaments):
    Euler chars χ(Ind) = I(Ω,-1): [1]
    f-vector (6x): f_0=1
    Topological amplification H/χ = 1/1 = 1.000
  H=3 (2 tournaments):
    Euler chars χ(Ind) = I(Ω,-1): [0]
    f-vector (2x): f_0=1, f_1=1

