======================================================================
PART 3: THE x-DEFORMATION — I(Ω, x) from topology to counting
======================================================================

I(Ω, -1) = Euler characteristic (topology)
I(Ω, 0) = 1 (trivial)
I(Ω, 1) = #independent sets (combinatorics)
I(Ω, 2) = H (tournament count)

The interpolation I(Ω, x) for x ∈ {-1, 0, 1, 2, 3} shows how
topology deforms into counting.

--- n = 5: Full interpolation table ---
   H  #cyc  I(-1)  I(0)  I(1)  I(2)   I(3)   I(4)
-------------------------------------------------------
   1     0      1     1     1     1      1      1
   3     1      0     1     2     3      4      5
   5     2     -1     1     3     5      7      9
   9     4     -3     1     5     9     13     17
  11     5     -4     1     6    11     16     21
  15     7     -6     1     8    15     22     29
  13     6     -5     1     7    13     19     25

